  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\n`truffle compile` won't compile vyper contracts in hidden directories (those start with a dot) after updating `contracts_directory` in `truffle-config.js`.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\nwith `vyper: 0.2.7+commit.0b3f3b3` and `Truffle v5.1.49` on macOS Catalina 10.15.6: \r\n```bash\r\n...\r\n\r\n# after setting up a toy npm playground\r\nnpx truffle init\r\n\r\n# simplest contract\r\necho \"i: public(uint256)\" >  contracts/Contract.vy\r\n\r\n# normal\r\nnpx truffle compile\r\n\r\nCompiling your contracts...\r\n===========================\r\n> Compiling ./contracts/Migrations.sol\r\n> Compiling ./contracts/Contract.vy\r\n> Artifacts written to build/contracts\r\n> Compiled successfully using:\r\n   - solc:  0.5.16+commit.9c3226ce.Emscripten.clang\r\n   - vyper: 0.2.7+commit.0b3f3b3\r\n\r\n\r\nrm -rf build\r\nmv contracts .contracts\r\nvim truffle-config.js  # update `contracts_directory` to `.contracts`\r\n\r\n# WEIRD: vyper contract is omitted\r\nnpx truffle compile\r\n\r\nCompiling your contracts...\r\n===========================\r\n> Compiling ./.contracts/Migrations.sol\r\n> Artifacts written to build/contracts\r\n> Compiled successfully using:\r\n   - solc: 0.5.16+commit.9c3226ce.Emscripten.clang\r\n\r\n```\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\n`Contract.vy` should be compiled.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\n...but it's not, while the solidity contract is compiled successfully as usual.\r\n\r\nthis bug matters because some tool is relying on `contracts_directory` for various reasons, e.g. https://github.com/sc-forks/solidity-coverage will create a folder `.coverage_contracts` and copy files there for compilation, and this bug will affect projects having vyper contracts  as a dependency using that tool.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: macOS Catalina 10.15.6\r\n* Ethereum client: NA\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): v5.1.49\r\n* node version (`node --version`): v12.19.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 6.14.8\r\n",
